Boipelo MerePolice in the Northern Cape are seeking assistance in tracking down the family of a man whose body was found in an open veld in Transit Camp on Sunday (23/04) at about 08:00.The body of an African man was allegedly found burnt in the veld by a passerby, who informed the police. According to the police, the deceased is estimated to be between 30 and 32 years old. The police have registered a case of murder for investigation. No arrests have yet been made. We appeal to the community to contact the investigating officer, Det.WO Surette Zandberg, on 082-469-0547, if they have any information regarding the incident or about the identity of the deceased, said Sgt Majang Skalkie.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.